body:
will there be an actual working version? now it's just look & feel.
what are the plans?

comment_data.body:
I am not an Android programmer, and I don't have much time to dig deeply into all the intricacies of the platform. There won't be a working version until the UI is stable. Currently, there are a few severe UI bugs that need to be resolved before I am willing to add actual network interaction. I have some ideas about how that network interaction will be done, and I'm actively working on the backend components.

If you know how to do Android UI programming or you have time and willingness to teach yourself, your contribution would be extremely valued.

Is this project still active?

If yes, I would like to contribute, I am also not an android dev, but I can learn

I saw antox on android, in which the last update was 2 years  ago....
Check out aTox at https://github.com/evilcorpltd/aTox and TRIfA at https://github.com/zoff99/ToxAndroidRefImpl, they're the two maintained android tox apps now.

title: actual working version
